title: Linked Plot Maps for Multivariate High Resolution Spatio-Temporal Data
text: example shows basic workflow making visualizations DrivePlotR. Load DrivePlotR make drive data available R session. made non-sensitive drives naturalistic driving study available part DrivePlotR package, data geographic temporal components also suitable. Establish geographic variables projection. code creates simple feature variable geometry points. Setting geographic projection WGS84 ensures points data line maps Leaflet. already done example dataset drive7 included package. Convert drive data shared data frame. Create visualizations. Although main purpose DrivePlotR users create linked visualizations map one four companion graphs, users can also separately create maps companion graphs. can create basic standalone map following code: can also create standalone companion graph follows: DrivePlotR offers many options customization. example, following code creates complex linked plot map. companion graphs include speed, gyroscopic heading (direction vehicle going), GPS position dilution precision (PDOP, measure quality GPS location data). points map companion graphs colored minute drive occurred.
code: library(DrivePlotR) data("drive7") shared_drive <- crosstalk::SharedData$new(drive7) driveplot_map(   shareddata = shared_drive ) driveplot_companion(   shareddata = shared_drive,    x = time_cst,    y = speed_mph,    xlabel = "Time",    ylabel = "Speed (MPH)" ) driveplot(   shareddata = shared_drive,    x = time_cst,    ys = c(speed_mph, gyro_heading, gps_pdop),   colorvar = gps_minute,    maplabel = time_cst,    colorpalette = "viridis",    xlabel = "Time",    ylabels = c("Speed (MPH)", "Gyro Heading", "GPS PDOP"),   showlegend = TRUE,    legendtitle = "Minute",    plottitle = "A Drive in Omaha, NE" )

Blackbox-Driving Data for one drive — drive7
text: tibble 321 rows 34 columns drive integer, identifier drive; drive defined time starting car turning time_utc POSIXct time stamp observation UTC time_cst POSIXct time stamp observation Central time GPS based measurements observation: gps_elevation numeric elevation sea-level (m) gps_heading numeric direction car (degrees) gps_fix numeric gps_sats integer, number satellites covering position gps_pdop numeric, total dilution precision gps_hdop numeric, horizontal dilution precision gps_vdop numeric, vertical dilution precision speed_mph numeric, speed vehicle (miles per hour) speed_source character, one "gps" "obd" distance_miles numeric, distance travelled drive (miles) Measurements -board gyroscope: accel_x numeric, forward acceleration (g) accel_y numeric, sidewards acceleration (g) accel_z numeric, upwards acceleration (g) accel_event binary, acceleration event occur? 0/1 accel_event_cat character, categorization acceleration event low, medium, high gyro_x numeric, angular rotation rate right--left axis (degrees/sec) gyro_y numeric, angular rotation rate forward--backward axis. gyro_z numeric, angular rotation rate --axis. gyro_heading numeric, calculated heading utilizing compass data gyro data (degrees). Note use non-standard congruence classes continuity consecutive values. grav_x numeric, lateral gravity (g) grav_y numeric, longitudinal gravity grav_z numeric, gravity (-) roll numeric, angle forward--backward axis. 0 = level, positive = tilted left pitch numeric, angle left--right axis. 0 = level, positive = tilted downward (.e., vehicle going downhill) engine_rpm numeric, current engine revolutions per minute value engine_throttle numeric, percentage engine throttle (0-100) cumulative_drive_dist_mi numeric gps_minute factor gps_heading_raw numeric, gps heading modulo 360 gyro_heading_raw numeric, gyro heading modulo 360 GPS coordinates simple features column: geometry list-column, simple features geometry column geometry type POINT
